  "title": "Airfreight Operations Executive [EL]",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Handle end-to-end airfreight operations from shipment booking to final delivery.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with airlines, ground handlers, transporters, and overseas agents.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, check, and process airfreight documents including AWB, manifests, and customs paperwork.</p></li><li><p>Ensure shipments comply with airline, customs, and regulatory requirements.</p></li><li><p>Monitor flight schedules and ensure timely cargo uplift and delivery.</p></li><li><p>Manage cargo handling, warehouse coordination, and delivery arrangements.</p></li><li><p>Resolve operational issues such as delays, rollovers, or documentation discrepancies.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate operational records and update systems accordingly.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with safety, quality, and internal SOPs.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Logistics, Supply Chain Management, or related discipline.</p></li><li>At least 1–3 years of hands-on experience in airfreight operations.</li><li>Good knowledge of airfreight procedures, documentation, and customs requirements.</li><li>Able to work independently and manage multiple shipments simultaneously.</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.</li><li>Comfortable with shift work or extended hours when required.</li></ul><p><br />We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p><p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
